HEADWORD: monovular
<hw>monovular</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>derived from
a single egg or ovum; -- of twins; <as>as, identical twins are
<ex>monovular</ex></as>. Contrasted with <ant>fraternal</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> identical.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

